bug.short_desc: Embedded images are not shown in Gmail web client

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem:
Embedded images in HTML messages are not shown in Gmail web client. They are shown as text (sometimes) or missing.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
3.16.5 (F22) and 3.18.x (F23)
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Write image in HTML, paste in graphics. 2. Send it to a user with gmail. 3.
Actual results:
Images are shown BASE64 strings, or missing.
Expected results: Images are seen.
Additional info:
Other email clients seem to be happy (at least the email reader Mac people use). But my collaborator that use Gmail web interface have been showing me this problem. Gmail is so widely used that even if it their fault we may need to come up with a workaround. Sad.

Hi, I tried to reproduce this issue (by inserting an image to the message with the Insert->Image dialog) and it works for me. I also copied and pasted some image from GIMP. Can you please specify a little bit more what "paste in graphic" means?
